[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMS: [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ; base unit: [0m[1;36m0000000000000000000000000000000000000000[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mxz[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpgxfqjb40[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz_encode_stream -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer test of the XZ library’s stream encoder [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz_encode_stream`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man AddressSanitizer error indicating a heap-use-after-free in the function [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile `treeck.c`, line [0m[1;36m79[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The invalid read of eight bytes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappens on a buffer region that was previously freed within the same checksum [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputation routine. The crash propagates through LZMA tree-check and [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream-encoding functions invoked by the fuzz harness.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis issue report documents an AddressSanitizer-detected heap-use-after-free in the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mXZ library’s internal checksum routines when running the `fuzz_encode_stream` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtarget under libFuzzer. The following observations summarize the relevant details:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Error type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – AddressSanitizer reports a read of size [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m from memory that has already been [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mheap-use-after-free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – The “SCARINESS” level is [0m[1;36m51[0m[39m, indicating a high-severity memory safety [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mviolation.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Faulting location  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – The invalid read occurs at `compute_tree_checksum` in [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/liblzma/check/treeck.[0m[1;92mc:79:34[0m[39m`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – This function is part of the LZMA tree-based integrity check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“Tree Check”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Allocation and free trace  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – A memory block of [0m[1;36m56[0m[39m bytes is allocated in `create_tree` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalled from [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`lzma_tree`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – The same block is freed during a recursive checksum computation in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m90[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – After the free, the code continues and attempts to read from the freed block at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m79[0m[39m.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Call chain leading to the crash  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz_encode_stream.c`  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `fuzz_code` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom `fuzz_common.h`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `lzma_code` in `common.c`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `stream_encode` in `stream_encoder.c`  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `block_encode` in `block_encoder.c`  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `lzma_check_update` in `check.c`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. `lzma_tree` in `treeck.c`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m. `compute_tree_checksum` in `treeck.c`  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Fuzz harness context  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – The harness sets up environment variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[33mFUZZING_ENGINE[0m[39m=[0m[35mlibfuzzer[0m[39m`, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mRUN_FUZZER_MODE[0m[39m=[0m[35minteractive[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and invokes the fuzzer with `-[0m[33mmax_len[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m4096[0m[39m`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – The harness itself is not the source of the bug but provides the entry point [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat triggers the failure in the library code.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Relevant code areas for investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – `src/liblzma/check/treeck.c`, especially the recursive logic in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` and its calls to `free`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – `src/liblzma/check/check.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`lzma_check_update`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand how checksums [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare updated across blocks.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – `src/liblzma/common/block_encoder.c` and `src/liblzma/common/stream_encoder.c` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor how the checksum routines are integrated into the encoding pipeline.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo speculation on root causes or fixes is included. The report focuses strictly on [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhat the log shows, where the issue manifests, and what components are involved.[0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer-based test of the `xz` library’s `fuzz_encode_stream` target triggered [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man AddressSanitizer heap-use-after-free in `compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/liblzma/check/treeck.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The attempted fix rewrote `compute_tree_checksum` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly free nodes after traversing children and to guard against double processing, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut the patch was misapplied [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline numbers were injected into the source[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. As a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresult, the build now fails with a syntax error [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“expected identifier or [0m[32m'[0m[32m([0m[32m'[0m[39m” on [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe spurious “[0m[1;36m66[0m[39m” prefix[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and implicit‐declaration warnings for [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During fuzzing with AddressSanitizer enabled, `fuzz_encode_stream` reported a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-use-after-free in `compute_tree_checksum` at treeck.[0m[1;92mc:79[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan’s stack trace showed that `compute_tree_checksum` both freed `node->edges` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `node` and then, in a recursive call from the parent, attempted to read from [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe already-freed child structure.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash chain:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `compute_tree_checksum` allocates a local tree structure via `create_tree`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Recursively visits children, frees them in post-order.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Returns to a parent invocation which still references the freed child memory. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log included full ASan output, memory addresses, allocation sites [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`malloc` in `create_tree`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and free sites [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `free` in `compute_tree_checksum`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the complete call stack from `lzma_tree` through `block_encode` and [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`stream_encode` to the fuzz harness.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch replaced the original `compute_tree_checksum` implementation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m93[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a new version starting at an indicated offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m66[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Key changes in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe diff:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Guard early when `node` is NULL or not in state `STATE_CLEAR`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Mark `node->state = STATE_VISITED`, recurse on children, then set to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`STATE_HASHED`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Free `node->edges` and `node` after processing.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The unified diff looked like this [0m[1;39m([0m[39mabridged[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  -static uint32_t [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node, unsigned int depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +[0m[1;36m66[0m[39m static uint32_t [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node, unsigned int depth[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +[0m[1;36m67[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe correct location of `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls to avoid use-after-free.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
